						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kannaradēva (Kṛishṇa III): Year 18 = 957 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of (1/4) <hi rend="italic">śey</hi> of land in the southern hamlet called Koliyūr of Śiṟṟiṅgūr, <hi rend="italic">a brahmadēya</hi> in Kuṟukkaik-kūṟṟam in Malāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jananātha-vaḷanāḍu, by the assembly <hi rend="italic">(sabhai)</hi> of the place to the dancing woman named Tiruppulippagavar Nirttaviṭaṅki and her descendants, as taxfree <hi rend="italic">nirttabōgam,</hi> for performing dance before the image of the god Tiruppulippagavar when it was taken out in procession.</p>						

						</summary>
